 Peru national football team Logo
The Peru national football team represents Peru in men’s international football. The national team has been organised, since 1927, by the Peruvian Football Federation. The FPF constitutes one of the ten members of FIFA’s South American Football Confederation. Peru has won the Copa América twice and qualified for FIFA World Cup finals five times; the team also participated in the 1936 Olympic football competition and has reached the semi-finals of the CONCACAF Gold Cup.
You can download theFPFlogo on full-version of the page.
